<h2>Latest News</h2>

<h3><a href="http://gnome3.org/index.html">GNOME 3 is Coming!</a></h3>
<p>The GNOME project has launched <a href="http://gnome3.org/index.html">a website</a> to provide information about the major new version of the GNOME desktop, which is scheduled for release in April 2011. The site is a great place to find out about the features of the new release, and contains screenshots and answers to commonly asked questions. Further content will be added in the future, including videos and the opportunity to download a live preview of the new desktop.</p>

<h3><a href="http://blogs.gnome.org/foundation/2010/11/16/gnome-foundation-is-hiring/">GNOME Foundation is seeking an Executive Director</a></h3>
<p>The GNOME Foundation is currently recruiting an Executive Director to
run and grow The GNOME Foundation and project by engaging volunteers,
governments, partners, companies and independent organizations. The
Executive Director will work to develop and maintain programs to
further GNOMEâ€™s goals, to promote the benefits of the GNOME platform,
and encourage contribution and collaboration within the GNOME
ecosphere. For details, including roles and responsibilities and where to send resumes, <a href="http://blogs.gnome.org/foundation/2010/11/16/gnome-foundation-is-hiring/">read the full announcement</a>.</p>

<h3><a href="/press/releases/2010-11-women-outreach-interns.html">GNOME Project Announces Outreach Program for Women Interns</a></h3>
<p>The GNOME project is proud to announce the participants of the Outreach Program for Women internships. Thanks to generous sponsors, Google, Collabora and the GNOME Foundation, GNOME was able to accept eight really strong candidates. Read the <a href="/press/releases/2010-11-women-outreach-interns.html">press release</a>.</p>

