<h2>Upcoming Events</h2>

<h3><a href="">GNOME 3.0 Bangalore Hackfest</a></h3>
<i>March 28 - April 1 2011, Bangalore, India</i>

<p>We are hosting a <strong>5 days hackfest</strong> for the release, documentation and marketing teams focusing on the <a
href="http://www.gnome3.org">GNOME 3.0</a> release. This will ensure some heavy testing of the code during the last week before the official release, as well as preparing the release to happen in an optimal way. And at the same time, it will help the marketing team to clarify messaging when needed and finalize the launch details.</p>

<p>It is not primarily aimed at users or new contributors but we may organize some training and hands on sessions during the last 3 days of the hackfest (March 30 to April 1). Apart from that, any contributor involved in the release process is strongly encouraged to join.<br/>
Please let us know you are coming by <a href="http://live.gnome.org/Hackfests/GNOME.Asia2011">registering on the hackfest page</a>.</p>

<h3><a href="http://www.desktopsummit.org/">Desktop Summit 2011</a></h3>
<i>August 6-12, 2011, Berlin, Germany</i>
<p>TThe Desktop Summit is the get-together of the yearly free software conferences Akademy and GUADEC. This year, the Desktop Summit will take place at the Humboldt University in Berlin. The event will feature keynotes, talks, workshops and social activities.</p>

<p>We expect well over a thousand participants, including core contributors, prominent open source technology leaders, representatives from government, education and corporate backgrounds, open source desktop engineers, usability experts and designers.</p>

